   Using the Extended Euclidean Algorithm, we find that the inverse of 31 modulo 2293 is 1859.

2. **Step 8.2: Multiply both sides of the congruence \( 31n \equiv 3 \pmod{2293} \) by the inverse found in Step 8.1.**

