- A number \( a \) is a perfect \( n^{\text{th}} \) power if \( a = b^n \) for some integer \( b \).
- Express \( 2^{24} \) in terms of \( n \): \( 2^{24} = (2^k)^n \) where \( k \cdot n = 24 \).

